narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Math 108 is a fantastic option for QR--it is interesting, enriching and allows students without the strongest background in math to engage with the material in a approachable but constructive way.
Yes, I would definitely recommend this course to another student. The content is interesting and engaging, while not overly difficult.
Math 108 is a class were y can learn a lot if you put your time in to it. This class is perfect if you don't want to take a Calculus.
Definitely take this course if you're looking for a QR credit that will refresh your math skills. It's a great way to go over problem-solving methods in a low-stress environment.

I would absolutely recommend this course to another student. It's a very good introduction to mathematical concepts that are critical to nearly any field, and the instructor is extremely helpful and skilled at explaining the material.
I would definitely recommend this class if you're a non-stem/math major who is a bit rusty on the basics. It's really fun, interesting and practical.
